-- Dubai Electricity Comprehensive Income Declines 1.7% as Finance Costs Rise
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-04-26T07:51:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/dubai-electricity-comprehensive-income-declines-1-7-as-finance-costs-rise.html

          
          
             Dubai Electricity and Water
Authority, the state-owned utility, said total comprehensive
income in 2009 fell 1.7 percent as finance costs surged.  
 The income dropped to 4.16 billion dirhams ($1.13 billion)
from 4.24 billion in the previous year, the utility said in a
statement posted on the Nasdaq Dubai Web site today. Revenue
rose 11 percent to 10.3 billion dirhams, while net finance costs
more than doubled to 1.04 billion dirhams from 460.2 million
dirhams  
